Creating images with R

with a little bit of magick

Wei Liang

2023-03-10

my meme

is about when I saw the dog’s reaction, I wanted to make a meme for it because I raised a dog at home. I used two different memes in different contexts. Such memes are quite common, but I think they are very interesting, so I also wanted to make one. image = 

library(magick)
#first meme
when_i_see_dog <- image_read("https://elcomercio.pe/resizer/Xgnd8XmM04H6qD7B7aZPeFtV6Ng=/580x330/smart/filters:format(jpeg):quality(75)/cloudfront-us-east-1.images.arcpublishing.com/elcomercio/VSKFMZULGJGOFESNU6DGAKDYFA.jpg") %>%
  image_resize("300x300!")
when_i_see_dog

#second meme
when_dog_come <- image_read("https://scontent-hkt1-2.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.6435-9/123576792_3732966220079840_7103153639622253486_n.jpg?_nc_cat=100&ccb=1-7&_nc_sid=9267fe&_nc_ohc=N-fcv2883ioAX-92sxt&_nc_ht=scontent-hkt1-2.xx&oh=00_AfDy1RxHCrkSie88NiXdosdUUwkvRSCx-ANdfAWsctPNeg&oe=643554B6")%>%
  image_resize("300x300!")
when_dog_come

#first text
#the box
dog_test <- image_blank(width = 300, height = 300, color = "#FFFFFF")%>%
  image_annotate(text = "When i see\na dog",
                 color = "#C0C0C0",
                 size = 50,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

#append image dog_test and when_i_see dog
top_meme <- image_append(c(dog_test, when_i_see_dog))
top_meme

dog_come <- image_blank(width = 300, height = 300, color = "#FFFFFF")%>%
  image_annotate(text = "when the dog\ncome to me",
                 color = "#C0C0C0",
                 size = 50,
                 font = "impact",
                 gravity = "center")

#append image dog_come and when_dog_come
down_meme <- image_append(c(dog_come, when_dog_come))
down_meme
dog_meme <- (c(top_meme, down_meme))%>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)%>%
  image_scale(400)
dog_meme

#save image
image_write(dog_meme, "my_meme.png")

image_animate(frame,fps = 2)
image_morph(frame)
frame <- c(dog_test, when_i_see_dog, dog_come, when_dog_come)
dog_gif_1 <- image_animate(frame, fps =2)
dog_gif_2 <- image_morph(frame)%>%
  image_animate(fps=100)

My animated GIF

The inspiration of animated animated GIF comes from my own memes. Firstly, I think animated memes will be very interesting. Secondly, I have written a series of codes of memes, so it will be more convenient for me to create animated GIF directly by using the codes of memes. image = 

image_animate(frame,fps = 2)
image_morph(frame)
frame <- c(dog_test, when_i_see_dog, dog_come, when_dog_come)
dog_gif_1 <- image_animate(frame, fps =2)
dog_gif_2 <- image_morph(frame)%>%
  image_animate(fps=50)
image_write(dog_gif_2, "my_animation.gif")
